#: ../../source/SoutheastAsia.ipynb:122
msgid "1. The scenario"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SoutheastAsia.ipynb:124
msgid ""
"The Lower Mekong basin spans five Southeast Asian countries with very "
"different power systems:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SoutheastAsia.ipynb:126
msgid ""
"**Cambodia, Laos, Myanmar** – small, hydro-dominant, mostly exporters "
"(especially Laos, the ‘battery of Southeast Asia’)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SoutheastAsia.ipynb:127
msgid "**Thailand, Vietnam** – large, fossil-heavy, importers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SoutheastAsia.ipynb:129
msgid ""
"The shared resource is the Mekong river system: 57 cascading hydropower "
"stations whose operation in one country affects downstream flows in "
"another. Adding a coal plant in Vietnam, expanding solar in Thailand, or "
"building a new dam in Laos all interact through the system-wide power "
"balance, the international transmission grid, and – in 2030 – a system-"
"wide 146 MtCO2 emission cap."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SoutheastAsia.ipynb:131
msgid ""
"PREP-SHOT models this as a single capacity-expansion linear program, "
"picking the least-cost technology mix in each country for each modeled "
"year subject to demand, fuel, transmission, reservoir, and carbon "
"constraints."
msgstr ""

